\begin_layout Standard
The regressions used thus far span the full sample from 1896–2018.
 Yet, female athlete attendance in the Olympic games has risen substantially
 in the past few decades as depicted in Figure 1.
 In the full sample, the typical female athlete is more representative of
 the modern Olympic era than the typical male athlete.
 A comparison between female and male athletes of the same era may be preferable.
 As a result, I break the sample into three distinct eras for comparison
